{"title_page": "Bill Hall Trail", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=November 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox hiking trail\n |name=Bill Hall trail\n |photo=\n |caption=\n |length=\n |location=[[Grand Canyon National Park]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]]\n |trailheads=[[Colorado River]]\n |use=[[Hiking]]\n |elev_change=\n |highest=\n |lowest=\n |difficulty=\n |season=\n |sights=[[Grand Canyon]]\n |hazards=[[Severe weather|Severe Weather]]<br>[[Fatigue (physical)|Overexertion]]<br>[[Dehydration]]<br>[[Flash flood|Flash Flood]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Bill Hall Trail''' is a [[hiking]] [[trail]] in [[Grand Canyon National Park]], located in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Arizona]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The Grand Canyon and the American Southwest: Trekking in the Grand Canyon, Zion and Bryce Canyon National Parks|first1=Constance |last1=Roos|first2= Bob |last2=Gibbons|first3= Sian |last3=Pritchard-Jones |edition=2|publisher =Cicerone Press Limited|year= 2008 |ISBN =1-85284-453-1|pages=88}}</ref>\n\n==Access==\nThe trail begins at ''Monument Point'' along the north rim of the canyon on the boundary of the National Park, about {{Convert|20|mi|km|0}} west of the park services at North Rim, Arizona.  Access to the trailhead is over {{Convert|35|mi|km|0}} of forest roads made of graded dirt, and a [[four-wheel drive]] vehicle is recommended for travel in the area. When roads are dry the trailhead can be accessed by a passenger car.\n\n==Description==\nFrom the dirt parking lot at the trailhead, the trail heads west and dips below the rim into the park.  The trail makes several short, steep switchbacks during its descent through the upper canyon rock layers.  In the Coconino Sandstone, the trail is at its steepest.  There are numerous boulders, some very large, that require care to detour around or climb over.  Some portions of this descent may require lowering of backpacks prior to downclimbing.\n\nAfter {{Convert|2|mi|km|0}} of steep descent, the trail levels off along the Esplanade Sandstone until the junction with the [[Thunder River Trail]].  This junction marks the lower terminus of the trail.\n\nThe trail is named for Bill Hall who was a seasonal park ranger on the North Rim who was killed in the line of duty (automobile accident) in \n1979.\n\n==See also==\n* [[The Grand Canyon]]\n* [[List of trails in Grand Canyon National Park]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.nps.gov/grca/ Grand Canyon National Park, Official site]\n* https://travelvagrants.com/bill-hall-trail/ Bill Hall trails]\n{{Coord|36.43461|-112.42933|type:landmark_region:US_scale:50000|display=title}}\n\n{{Grand Canyon trails}}\n\n[[Category:Hiking trails in Grand Canyon National Park]]\n[[Category:Grand Canyon, North Rim]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=November 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox hiking trail\n |name=Bill Hall trail\n |photo=\n |caption=\n |length=\n |location=[[Grand Canyon National Park]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]]\n |trailheads=[[Colorado River]]\n |use=[[Hiking]]\n |elev_change=\n |highest=\n |lowest=\n |difficulty=\n |season=\n |sights=[[Grand Canyon]]\n |hazards=[[Severe weather|Severe Weather]]<br>[[Fatigue (physical)|Overexertion]]<br>[[Dehydration]]<br>[[Flash flood|Flash Flood]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Bill Hall Trail''' is a [[hiking]] [[trail]] in [[Grand Canyon National Park]], located in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Arizona]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The Grand Canyon and the American Southwest: Trekking in the Grand Canyon, Zion and Bryce Canyon National Parks|first1=Constance |last1=Roos|first2= Bob |last2=Gibbons|first3= Sian |last3=Pritchard-Jones |edition=2|publisher =Cicerone Press Limited|year= 2008 |ISBN =1-85284-453-1|pages=88}}</ref>\n\n==Access==\nThe trail begins at ''Monument Point'' along the north rim of the canyon on the boundary of the National Park, about {{Convert|20|mi|km|0}} west of the park services at North Rim, Arizona.  Access to the trailhead is over {{Convert|35|mi|km|0}} of forest roads made of graded dirt, and a [[four-wheel drive]] vehicle is recommended for travel in the area. When roads are dry the trailhead can be accessed by a passenger car.\n\n==Description==\nFrom the dirt parking lot at the trailhead, the trail heads west and dips below the rim into the park.  The trail makes several short, steep switchbacks during its descent through the upper canyon rock layers.  In the Coconino Sandstone, the trail is at its steepest.  There are numerous boulders, some very large, that require care to detour around or climb over.  Some portions of this descent may require lowering of backpacks prior to downclimbing.\n\nAfter {{Convert|2|mi|km|0}} of steep descent, the trail levels off along the Esplanade Sandstone until the junction with the [[Thunder River Trail]].  This junction marks the lower terminus of the trail.\n\nThe trail is named for Bill Hall who was a seasonal park ranger on the North Rim who was killed in the line of duty (automobile accident) in \n1979.\n\n==See also==\n* [[The Grand Canyon]]\n* [[List of trails in Grand Canyon National Park]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.nps.gov/grca/ Grand Canyon National Park, Official site]\n* http://www.xmission.com/~mbmiles/p165.htm Bill Hall, Thunder River and Deer Creek trails][[dead link]]\n{{Coord|36.43461|-112.42933|type:landmark_region:US_scale:50000|display=title}}\n\n{{Grand Canyon trails}}\n\n[[Category:Hiking trails in Grand Canyon National Park]]\n[[Category:Grand Canyon, North Rim]]\n", "name_user": "Nipunadk123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Old Dead Link Removed and added New Link About Bill Hall Trails", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Hall_Trail"}
{"title_page": "University of Cincinnati Department of Chemistry", "text_new": "{{primary sources|date=March 2008}}\n{{Infobox university|\nname=University of Cincinnati<br>\nDepartment of Chemistry|\nimage=|\nestablished=1874|\nhead_label=Acting Chair|\nhead=Patrick Limbach|\nfaculty=26|\nundergrad=30|\npostgrad=100|\nother=7| \ncity=[[Cincinnati, Ohio|Cincinnati]]|\nstate=[[Ohio]]|\ncountry=[[United States]]|\nwebsite=http://www.che.uc.edu|\n}}\nThe '''University of Cincinnati Department of Chemistry''' is the [[chemistry]] department of the [[University of Cincinnati College of Arts and Sciences|College of Arts and Sciences]] at the [[University of Cincinnati]] in [[Cincinnati, Ohio|Cincinnati]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]]. Founded in 1874, the department awarded its first [[bachelor of science]] and [[master of science]] degrees in 1880. In 1905, it awarded its first [[Ph.D]].\n\nIt is a Carnegie Foundation-designated Doctoral/Research-Extensive institution.\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.che.uc.edu/ University of Cincinnati Department of Chemistry official website]\n*[http://bessie.che.uc.edu/wiki Wiki style website]\n{{University of Cincinnati}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:University of Cincinnati]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1874]]\n[[Category:1874 establishments in Ohio]]\n\n\n{{Ohio-university-stub}}\n{{Cincinnati-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{primary sources|date=March 2008}}\n{{Infobox university|\nname=University of Cincinnati<br>\nDepartment of Chemistry|\nimage=|\nestablished=1874|\nhead_label=Acting Chair|\nhead=Patrick Limbach|\nfaculty=26|\nundergrad=30|\npostgrad=100|\nother=7| \ncity=[[Cincinnati, Ohio|Cincinnati]]|\nstate=[[Ohio]]|\ncountry=[[United States]]|\nwebsite=http://www.che.uc.edu|\n}}\nThe '''University of Cincinnati Department of Chemistry''' is the [[chemistry]] department of the [[McMicken College of Arts and Sciences]] at the [[University of Cincinnati]] in [[Cincinnati, Ohio|Cincinnati]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]]. Founded in 1874, the department awarded its first [[bachelor of science]] and [[master of science]] degrees in 1880. In 1905, it awarded its first [[Ph.D]].\n\nIt is a Carnegie Foundation-designated Doctoral/Research-Extensive institution.\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.che.uc.edu/ University of Cincinnati Department of Chemistry official website]\n*[http://bessie.che.uc.edu/wiki Wiki style website]\n{{University of Cincinnati}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:University of Cincinnati]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1874]]\n[[Category:1874 establishments in Ohio]]\n\n\n{{Ohio-university-stub}}\n{{Cincinnati-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Janus657", "label": "safe", "comment": "Update A&S name", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Cincinnati_Department_of_Chemistry"}
